<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14974] Unit test stdout capture is malfunctioning in 4.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14974</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In 3.x unit tests we make sure to capture stdout to the unit test files, in case tests log to stdout and not to a logger. &#160;However, in 4.0 due to a configuration parameter that is deprecated in logback, the logic is short-circuited silently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once fixed, this affects the cleanup of in-jvm dtests which would register an infinite chain of System.out overrides&#160;(one for each node), so we make the functionality robust to multiple instantiations, as well as improve its startup/shutdown sequence guarantees.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
